cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new authentication solution for mobile devices with a focus on security against smudge attacks. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the usability and user acceptance of the proposed solution. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as the paper uses graphical images as password tokens and discusses the positioning of these images. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also possible as the paper uses graphical images as a means of authentication. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the memorability of the proposed solution.
